JavaScript doesn&#39;t support anything like an implicit `this`; therefore in `calcBMI`, `mass` and `height` are undefined. Also, you&#39;re defining a `mass` and `height` parameter, but when you&#39;re calling `mark.calcBMI`, you&#39;re not _passing arguments_ for those parameters.

It should also be noted that `^` is the XOR operator. The exponentiation operator is `**`.

Try this instead:

```
var mark = {
    firstName: &#39;Mark&#39;,
    height: 6.2,
    mass: 180,
    calcBMI: function() {
        this.BMI = this.mass / (this.height * this.height);
    }
};

mark.calcBMI();
console.log(mark);
```

    var mark = {
        firstName: &#39;Mark&#39;,
        height: 6.2,
        mass: 180,
        calcBMI: function() {
            this.BMI = this.mass / (Math.pow(this.height,2));
        }
    };
    
    mark.calcBMI();
    console.log(mark);

Just need to add `this` to the beginning and use `Math.pow()` instead of the `^` since that is the XOR operator, not the exponentiation operator.

